# Architecture

## Folder structure

```yml
landing-page/
  app/
    (routes)/
      page-name/
        page.tsx          ← thin: imports the page component, no logic
  components/
    ui/                   ← Shadcn primitives only, never modified directly
    page-name/            ← mirrors app/(routes)/page-name/
      PageNameHero.tsx
      PageNameFeatures.tsx
    shared/               ← reused across multiple pages like Footer, Navbar, ...
```

**Rule:** every `app/**/page.tsx` must have a matching folder under `components/`.
The page file only wires layout + data; all UI lives in components.

## Component rules

- Functional components only, no class components
- One component per file, named export preferred
- Props typed with `interface` (not inline), suffix `Props`
- Use Shadcn primitives before building custom ones
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for class merging — never string concat
- Extract custom hooks to `hooks/` when logic exceeds ~15 lines

```tsx
// ✅
interface HeroProps {
  title: string
  cta: string
}
export function Hero({ title, cta }: HeroProps) { … }

// ❌
export default function ({ title, cta }: { title: string; cta: string }) { … }
```

## CSS / Design tokens

- All colors, spacing, radii → CSS variables in `app/globals.css`
- Never hardcode hex or pixel values in components
- Dark mode via `next-themes`, toggle via `ThemeProvider`

## TypeScript

- `strict: true` always
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type guard if needed
- Prefer `const` assertions and `satisfies` over type casting
